-- Mali Approves $50 Million in Loans for Health and Infrastructure
-- B y   D i a k a r i d i a   D e m b e l e
-- 2012-10-18T03:09:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-18/mali-approves-50-million-in-loans-for-health-and-infrastructure.html
The government of  Mali  approved 24.9
billion CFA francs ($49.5 million) in loans from the Islamic
Development Bank and Islamic Solidarity Fund for health,
infrastructure, education and rural finance development.  The cabinet approved the loans after a meeting yesterday in
the capital of Bamako, according to an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Diakaridia Dembele in Johannesburg at 
 ddembele@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
